Adjust rack to middle position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Place @butter{2%tbsp} in a #small bowl{}; set aside to soften (you'll use it in step 6). Wash and dry produce.

Place @butter{1%tbsp} in a #medium microwave-safe bowl{}; microwave until melted, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in a large drizzle of @cooking oil{}, @Sweet and Smoky BBQ Seasoning{2%tsp}, a big pinch of @salt{}, and @pepper{}. (You'll use the remaining BBQ Seasoning later.) Add @panko breadcrumbs{1/2%cup} and stir until evenly combined.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with salt and pepper. Place in 1 #oven-ready aluminum tray{}.

Evenly spread @sour cream{2%tbsp} onto tops of chicken; mound with panko mixture, pressing to adhere (no need to coat the undersides).

Roast on middle rack until browned and cooked through, ~{20-25%minutes}. (You'll start the biscuits after 10 minutes.)

Meanwhile, cut @broccoli florets{8%oz} into bite-size pieces if necessary.

Place in another oven-ready aluminum tray; drizzle with oil and season with salt and pepper. Add @water{2%tbsp} to tray, then cover tightly with #foil{}.

Add to middle rack; roast until broccoli is tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Remove @Buttermilk Biscuits{6%oz} from package; spread out evenly in remaining oven-ready aluminum tray.

Once chicken has roasted 10 minutes, add biscuits to middle rack. Bake until golden brown, ~{12-15%minutes}.

While biscuits bake, add remaining @Sweet and Smoky BBQ Seasoning{1%tsp} to #bowl{} with softened butter. Season with salt and pepper; stir to combine.

Divide chicken, broccoli, and biscuits between #plates{}. Drizzle chicken with as much @Mike's Hot Honey®{3/4%oz} as you like. Serve biscuits with BBQ butter.

> Crispy panko-coated chicken, barbecue-buttered biscuits, and easy-peasy roasted broccoli are a pretty obvious recipe for dinnertime success. It's got your classic trifecta of meat, carb, and veg—could you ask for much more? How about a drizzle of hot honey? The stuff combines sweet sensations with spicy good vibrations, making it perfect for taking things beyond ordinary.